sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User/Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Envoy as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP TLS Terminate
    participant EF as EnvoyFilter<br/>ext_authz
    participant KAP as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth/OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Component<br/>(via HTTPRoute)

    Note over User,Upstream: Flow 1: Platform Ingress Authentication (Gateway API)

    User->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Envoy: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS termination
    Envoy->>EF: ext_authz check<br/>(internal)
    EF->>KAP: HTTPS/8443<br/>Bearer Token check
    KAP->>OAuth: HTTPS/443<br/>OAuth2 client creds<br/>TLS 1.2+
    OAuth-->>KAP: Token validated
    KAP->>K8sAPI: HTTPS/443<br/>TokenReview<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>KAP: Review result
    KAP-->>EF: Auth decision
    EF-->>Envoy: Authorized
    Envoy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>(via HTTPRoute)<br/>Auth headers forwarded
    Upstream-->>Envoy: Response
    Envoy-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant Webhook as DSC Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller
    participant Manifests as Kustomize Manifests<br/>/opt/manifests-template

    Note over Admin,Manifests: Flow 2: Component Deployment via DSC

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply DSC<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate DSC<br/>HTTPS/9443, mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission allowed
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: DSC created
    K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch event (DSC)
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Component CR<br/>(e.g., Dashboard, KServe)
    K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch event (Component CR)
    CompCtrl->>Manifests: Read kustomize manifests<br/>(filesystem)
    Manifests-->>CompCtrl: Rendered manifests
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Apply manifests<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>ServiceAccount Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Resources created

    participant OTel as OTel Collector<br/>(TargetAllocator)
    participant Pods as Component Pods<br/>(scrape=true)
    participant Prom as MonitoringStack<br/>(Prometheus)
    participant Thanos as ThanosQuerier<br/>10901/TCP gRPC
    participant NSProxy as Namespace Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard/UI

    Note over OTel,Dashboard: Flow 3: Monitoring Metrics Collection

    OTel->>Pods: Scrape metrics<br/>HTTP (varies)<br/>monitoring.opendatahub.io/scrape=true
    Pods-->>OTel: Metrics data
    OTel->>Prom: OTLP HTTP/4318<br/>TLS
    Thanos->>Prom: gRPC/10901<br/>TLS<br/>Federated query
    Prom-->>Thanos: Metrics response
    Dashboard->>NSProxy: HTTPS/8443<br/>Bearer Token
    NSProxy->>NSProxy: kube-rbac-proxy<br/>SubjectAccessReview
    NSProxy->>Prom: HTTPS/9090<br/>TLS (service-CA)
    Prom-->>NSProxy: Metrics
    NSProxy-->>Dashboard: Authorized metrics
